cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

The paper discusses a new neural language model that incorporates both word order and character order in its embedding, which is a common topic in the field of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also mentions the use of parallel training methods and the large size of the neural network, which suggests that it may also belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper's focus on word embeddings and their performance on a word-analogy task may also place it in sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
